<!--
date:7/19/2023 
Introduction to Html
Basic syntax
Tags:
Text formatting tags:
These tags are used to format or modify the text
b-bold
i-italic
u-underline
mark
em-emphazise
del-delete
sup-superscript
sub-subscript
small
big
order list
Anchor tag:
Anchor tag <a>URL</a> is used to redirect for any url or webpages
In anchor target is one of the attribute used to open the webiste or the external link in the new tab
List:
There are three types of list tags on html, it is used to show the group of elements
Ordered list- It displays the serial numbers like 1,2,3 etc. <ol> <li>content1</li>.....</ol>
if you want roman numbers or alphabets you have to activate the style attributes
Example:
<ol type="I">
    <li>
        heading1
    </li>
</ol>
output:
I Heading 
Unordered list- It doesnt display the serial number, it displays dot symbol. <ul> <li>content1</li>.....</ul>
Description list- To have a detailed information. <dl> <dt>Description heading</dt> <dd>Description conetent</dd>.....</dll>
Image:

-->

<!Doctype html>
<html>
    
    <head>
         <!--Title tag represents the name of the webpage, title tag is commonly used in head tag-->
        <title>
            Introduction to HTML
        </title>
    </head>

    <body>

      <!-- The entire content is present in the body tag   -->
      <!-- Heading tags are used to show the headings -->
      <!-- Heading tag contains a range from h1 to h6 -->
      <!-- To place a heading or content in the center of the webpage we use center tag -->
      <!-- To create a Horizontal line we use HR tag -->
      <!-- To create a paragraph we use P tag -->
      <!-- Break BR is a self closing tag, it used to create gaps between the paragraph or the content-->

      <center>

        <h1>
            <!-- H1 is the highest sized tag -->
            Heading 1 
          </h1>
          <h2>
            Heading 2
          </h2>
          <h3>
            Heading 3
          </h3>
          <h4>
            Heading 4
          </h4>
          <h5>
            Heading 5
          </h5>
          <h6>
            <!-- H6 is the lowest sized tag -->
            Heading 6
          </h6>
      </center>

      <!-- Anchor tag <a>URL</a> is used to redirect for any url or webpages, files. Target is one if the attribute it opens the external link in the new tab-->
      <a href="../filhtml.html" target="_blank">Click here</a>

      <ol type="I">
        <li>
            heading1
            <ol>
                head1
            </ol>
        </li>
        <li>
            heading2
        </li>
      </ol>

      </ol>
    </body>

</html>






<!Doctype html>
<html>
    
    <head>
         <!--Title tag represents the name of the webpage, title tag is commonly used in head tag-->
        <title>
            Introduction to HTML
        </title>
    </head>

    <body>

      <!-- The entire content is present in the body tag   -->
      <!-- Heading tags are used to show the headings -->
      <!-- Heading tag contains a range from h1 to h6 -->
      <!-- To place a heading or content in the center of the webpage we use center tag -->
      <!-- To create a Horizontal line we use HR tag -->
      <!-- To create a paragraph we use P tag -->
      <!-- Break BR is a self closing tag, it used to create gaps between the paragraph or the content-->

      <center>

        <h1>
            <!-- H1 is the highest sized tag -->
            Heading 1 
          </h1>
          <h2>
            Heading 2
          </h2>
          <h3>
            Heading 3
          </h3>
          <h4>
            Heading 4
          </h4>
          <h5>
            Heading 5
          </h5>
          <h6>
            <!-- H6 is the lowest sized tag -->
            Heading 6
          </h6>
      </center>


    </body>

</html>
